node.text:
What people see: a special opportunity seeing the new 400z and having a chance to sit in it giving me such nostalgic vibes!

What people don’t see: The cold emails I sent to Nissan execs and PR last October doing whatever I could to have a CHANCE to see this car in person. My industry friends know because I’ve reached out to almost all of them seeing what I could do to have the opportunity. Thank you @seanlee768 for having me out! Can’t wait to see these on the streets 🎌

node.text:
I’m so grateful of the people and companies I can call friends in this industry. I would look up to @sheepeyrace and their Honda work well before starting on YouTube (If you scroll back years on my IG you’ll see a post of mine admiring their weld work back in 2015) and to see everything Alex Soto has built over the years is nothing short of inspiring. A staple in the Lamborghini/ supercar industry, a NEW major facility, a full staff he employs, and more. 

Last week we brought Phoenix in for a “simple” dyno day… which turned into headache after headache and eventually leaving the car at his facility where he welcomed us to use his lift, tools, dyno, and whatever we needed. Thank you for the hospitality @sheepeyrace 🙏🏼 this led to us getting everything fixed and making over 1200 horsepowers!!!!

node.text:
In case you missed the YouTube video… WE REBROKE THE WORLD RECORD FOR HIGHEST HORSEPOWER C8 CORVETTE!!! It was honestly pretty nuts. We seem to have completely worked around any restrictions with the motor and put down an easy 1,201 whp and 1,057 ft-lb torque!! We could’ve pushed much more but are still on a stock crank and didn’t want to risk the engine 😅 thank you @sheepeyrace for the major hospitality and thank you everyone for believing in us 🙏🏼🙏🏼

node.text:
Thank you everyone who took the time out of their day to go see the @motulusa billboard and either taking a photo with it or sharing the awesome opportunity (sorry I couldn’t repost everyone 😢). 

Motul shared with me that since announcing our partnership they’ve seen a 4000% increase in Instagram traffic and the highest engagement to date!! 

We are working on a easy way for you at home to easy get your hands on the renowned 300V oil that I’ve been using in all my cars for years, so stay tuned on that! In the meantime you can do a search on their website for local suppliers 😇

This is such a huge step in the aftermarket automotive industry and I honestly feel so blessed to be a part of the journey.

node.text: Day 5 of “Cruisin’ the USA in Your Chevrolet” is live on the @Chevrolet page! #sponsored I have to admit, exploring @aloppen’s garage (also known as Camaroland), was such an unforgettable experience. From a restored Gen l to a 001 Vin Gen Vl, it’s hard not to get excited about the future! How would you folks at home design a new Gen Vll? What motor? Any power adders? EV?? #ChevyLove

node.text:
While in Michigan filming with the @Chevrolet team for “Cruising the USA in your Chevrolet,” I was asked if I had any unique memories or experiences with the Bolt EV- obviously, answer would be no way, right? #Sponsored

Well actually, not long before my dad passed, I have a very vivid memory of him showing me the first Chevy Bolt EV concept car and how excited he was for the future of EV. Cars didn’t run in the family for me, and at the time I wasn’t the gear head I am today. Tbh I thought the thing was a space ship and never going to happen. But his excitement stuck with me. I wish he could see me today… with the Bolt EUV and E-10 Concept. #ChevyLove #BoltEUV
